<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAUDIS SECRET STAKE IN MARINA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Saudi Arabia's embassy in the United States has great respect for the accuracy 
and responsibility of The Times but would like to clarify a reference in the 
article of Nov. 12, regarding a report that two Saudi businessmen had made an 
investment in Southern California for a younger son of the king. The young man 
is 16 years old and still in school. Neither he nor anyone else has authorized 
any Saudi, American nor other business person to handle any financial matter on 
the young man's behalf in this situation nor any other one. 
</P>
<P>
With regard to another part of the article, the embassy also wants to reiterate 
its government's firm position that no agent, whether Saudi or foreign, is 
allowed in connection with any Saudi defense purchase. 
</P>
<P>
As to the rest of the article, the embassy does not comment on the business 
activities of Saudi firms or individuals or of Americans doing business in 
Saudi Arabia so long as those activities do not violate our laws or those of 
the host country. 
</P>
<P>
HABIB A . SHAHEEN 
</P>
<P>
Director, Office of Information Embassy of Saudi Arabia 
</P>
<P>
Washington, D.C. 
</P>
</TEXT>
