<P>
TEACHING EVOLUTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
(State Supt. of Public Instruction) Bill Honig is to be commended for his 
change of position regarding the teaching of evolution. I also agree that we 
should not withhold scientific facts from our children, but let's be sure we 
teach all sides of the issue -- those things that are proven facts along with 
those that remain theories. To say that evolution in total is a fact is just 
not a true statement. 
</P>
<P>
HERBERT H. LEWIS 
</P>
<P>
Ventura 
</P>
