<P>
MORNING REPORT: STAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Shauna Snow, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Acting for AIDS Funds: Actors and theater companies across the nation have 
scheduled special events this week to raise funds for members of Actors Equity 
who have AIDS. The annual Actors Equity Fights AIDS Week, today through Sunday, 
will see the theater community involved with bake sales, flea markets, craft 
fairs, raffles, car washes, memorabilia and poster sales. Cabaret performances 
will also raise awareness and funds. Some companies will make audience appeals 
for donations at performance intermissions. Since setting up its Equity Fights 
AIDS fund-raising organization in 1987, the actors' union has raised $600,000, 
which has been distributed directly to more than 500 Equity members to offset 
medical and other expenses. Shauna Snow 
