<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: RESTAURANT FIRE CAUSES $40,000 DAMAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A fire that started in a deep-fat fryer forced the evacuation of a Thousand 
Oaks restaurant and caused $40,000 in damage, authorities said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Ventura County fire dispatcher Vicki Crabtree said the blaze, which did not 
cause any injuries, was reported about 7:30 p.m. Saturday in the kitchen of the 
El Torito restaurant at 449 N. Moorpark Road. It was brought under control 
about half an hour later by 36 firefighters. 
</P>
<P>
An automatic fire extinguisher in a heat hood over the fryer was activated but 
was unable to put out the blaze, which spread to the rest of the kitchen, 
Crabtree said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
