<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: SMALL QUAKE CENTERED NEAR GRANADA HILLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A small earthquake shook the San Fernando Valley on Sunday, but Caltech 
Seismology Lab officials said there were no reports of injuries or property 
damage. 
</P>
<P>
The quake, which struck at 12:39 p.m., measured 2.5 and was centered 1 mile 
northeast of Granada Hills. Police said they received several calls from 
residents who felt the earthquake. 
</P>
</TEXT>
