<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 61 ARRESTED IN PACOIMA PROSTITUTION STING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sixty-one men were arrested during a weekend sweep for allegedly soliciting 
prostitutes in Pacoima, Los Angeles police reported Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
The men were taken into custody after approaching three female officers posing 
as prostitutes on San Fernando Road between Van Nuys Boulevard and Osborne 
Street from noon to midnight Saturday, said Sgt. Ken Dionne. 
</P>
<P>
The men were either jailed at the Los Angeles Police Department's Foothill 
Division or cited and released pending a court appearance, Dionne said. He said 
the sweep was launched after vice officers noticed an increase in prostitution 
in the area. Forty prostitutes have been arrested on San Fernando Road in the 
past three weeks, police said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA112089-0059 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 137434 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
November 20, 1989, Monday, San Diego County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
