<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLEMAN SCORES 23 TO LEAD TROJANS OVER BRAZILIANS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ronnie Coleman had 23 points and nine rebounds to lead USC to an 83-78 victory 
over Nosso of Brazil in an exhibition game Sunday night at Rancho Santiago 
College. 
</P>
<P>
Robert Pack added 20 points and seven assists while Chris Munk had 12 points 
and seven rebounds for the Trojans. 
</P>
<P>
USC led, 41-31, at halftime, but Nosso tied the game at 63 with 8:56 to play on 
a three-pointer by Carlos Romano, who led his team with 23 points. Munk tipped 
in an offensive rebound with 44 seconds remaining to put the Trojans in front 
for good. 
</P>
</TEXT>
