</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
15-Year Home-Stake Case Ends: A federal judge in Tulsa, Okla., ordered five 
former officers of Home-Stake Production Co. to pay more than $127 million in 
damages to 1,600 people -- including several celebrities -- who were bilked. 
The case was initiated when the oil drilling tax shelter went sour in 1974, and 
the judgment brought down the curtain on prosecution of one of the largest 
Ponzi scheme cases ever. There were originally 39 defendants in the case, but 
some settled in 1982 and 1984. 
</P>
