<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWS WATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Dana Parsons and Steve Emmons 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JITTERS: Orange County residents are so accustomed to their own dangerous 
earthquake fault (the Newport-Inglewood) that the Bay Area quake a month ago 
has hardly affected them, right? Wrong. . . . The four major insurers of Orange 
County homes report increased interest in quake insurance: State Farm says 
business has doubled since the quake, Farmers says business is up by about 
250%, and Allstate and Aetna say queries are way up, although sales figures are 
not in. Dana Parsons and Steve Emmons 
</P>
