<HEADLINE>
<P>
4 DIE IN SANTA ANA AFTER CAR SLAMS INTO POLE DURING DRAG RACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SANTA ANA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At least four people died instantly in a ball of flame Sunday night when their 
car smashed into a telephone pole in Santa Ana and the gas tank exploded. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Ana Police Sgt. Doyle Smith said the driver of the car, a light blue Ford 
Maverick, had been drag-racing north on Bristol Street and lost control near 
Park Lane. The Maverick, containing at least four people, burst into flames 
when the gas ignited, Smith said. 
</P>
<P>
The other car in the drag race left the scene. Police said they are looking for 
the driver of a black Corvette. Police station Supervisor Richard Coberly said 
that according to witnesses, the driver of the Corvette "stopped and watched 
the car burning a litle bit and then split." 
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred at 10:45 p.m. Police did not yet know the names of the 
dead. 
</P>
<P>
All lanes of Bristol Street from Memory Lane to 17th Street were expected to be 
closed to traffic for at least four hours. 
</P>
</TEXT>
