LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
3 KILLED IN FRAZIER PARK CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two men and a pregnant woman died today when the car in which they were riding 
smashed into the back of a truck parked by the side of the Golden State Freeway 
south of Frazier Park, the California Highway Patrol said. 
</P>
<P>
The victims, whose names were not released pending notification of their 
relatives, were driving south on the Golden State Freeway at about 55 m.p.h. 
shortly after midnight when their car swerved to the right and rammed into the 
back of an 18-wheeler parked on the shoulder, said CHP Officer Mark Ehly. 
</P>
<P>
The driver, a 28-year-old Huntington Beach man, apparently fell asleep at the 
wheel, Ehly said. 
</P>
<P>
The truck was parked by the side of the road because it ran out of fuel, he 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The two passengers were identified only as a 25-year-old man and a 26-year-old 
Huntington Beach woman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
