CZECH DISSIDENT REJECTS VISA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PRAGUE, Czechoslovakia 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Leading Czechoslovak dissident Vaclav Havel said today he had been offered a 
passport to travel to Sweden to accept an award but had declined because of the 
situation in his country. 
</P>
<P>
Havel, an internationally known playwright, told a news conference in Prague: 
"I will not make use of the passport because the situation at home is becoming 
dramatic. I do not want to serve as a front for this regime, which would claim 
they let a leading dissident travel abroad, and thus try to mask the drastic 
repressions we are witnessing." 
</P>
